# Security Notes:
# - SSL Mode Options: disable, allow, prefer, require, verify-ca, verify-full
# - For development: use sslmode=disable or sslmode=prefer (no TLS)
# - For production: use sslmode=require or sslmode=verify-full (with TLS)
# - SECRET must be at least 32 characters (cryptographically secure random value)
#
# Redis TLS Configuration:
# - Use redis:// scheme for non-TLS connections (development/local)
# - Use rediss:// scheme for TLS connections (production)
# - Example with TLS: rediss://user:password@localhost:6379
# - Example without TLS: redis://user:password@localhost:6379
# - PostgreSQL connections use TLS based on sslmode parameter
